Skeleton of a Java Program

The basic syntax of a java program is as follows:

package packageName
class ClassName
{
    access_specifier return type functionName(Parameters)
    {
        //Java Code that does stuff
    }
}

Java requires some packages to run a program and one of those package is the java.lang package
The java.lang package is a mandatory package that is required to run a program.
The compiler will add this automatically even if the developer does not.

The main method is the starting type of the program and it is always void as this is the only function that never returns a value to another function
In a print statement in Java, we write a class, an object and a function to print something
That statement is: System.out.println();
System is a class that calls out which is an object and finally println() is a function.
A key point to note is that when you declare a class as public, the filename should match the name of the class otherwise an error will arise that will not let your program to execute


Reading Input from keyboard:

To read input from keyboard we need to include the Scanner class
To use the scanner class, we need to first import the util package and then create an object for the Scanner Class
Syntax: Scanner variable = new Scanner(System.in);
The System.in is the code needed to read input from the keyboard.

